      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but some people say that's not just \"deadlock,\" but that the whole system is actually broken and outdated because it just protects the interests of a few powerful countries while letting everything else fall apart. do historians see that as a valid critique of the UN's legitimacy, or is that just seen as a fringe view?",
